{"title_page": "Lord, You Have Come to the Lakeshore", "text_new": "{{Orphan|date=July 2016}}\n\n'''Lord, You Have Come to the Lakeshore''', in some versions '''You Have Come to the Seashore''' (Spanish: ''Pescador de hombres'', \"Fisher of Men\") is a 1974 [[Spain|Spanish]] religious song by Ces\u00e1reo Gabar\u00e1in. It was translated into English by Gertrude C. Suppe, George Lockwood and Raquel Guti\u00e9rrez-Achon.<ref name=\"Hymn\">Hymn Society of America, ed. (1995). ''[https://books.google.com.ar/books?id=K28JAQAAMAAJ&q=%22Pescador+de+hombres%22+%22Ces%C3%A1reo+Gabar%C3%A1in%22&dq=%22Pescador+de+hombres%22+%22Ces%C3%A1reo+Gabar%C3%A1in%22&hl=es&sa=X&ei=gDz3U6vZOoq6ogS8ioKoDA&ved=0CGAQ6AEwCQ The Hymn. Volume 46]</ref>\n\nIt was [[Pope John Paul II]]'s favourite song.<ref name=\"Pijarzy\"/>, and the Polish lyrics (titled ''Barka'', \"The Barge\") were written by a [[Salesians of Don Bosco|Salesian of Don Bosco]] Stanis\u0142aw Szmidt also in 1974<ref name=\"Pijarzy\">{{cite web|url=http://www.pijarzy.pl/polecamy/w_wolnym_czasie/czy_wiesz_ze.../%22barka%22_-_ulubiona_piesn_jana_pawla_ii,_historia_piesni_d7353_pol.html|title=\"Barka\" - ulubiona pie\u015b\u0144 Jana Paw\u0142a II, historia pie\u015bni|first=|last=netsoftware.pl|publisher=}}</ref>.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Spanish songs]]\n[[Category:Christian songs]]\n[[Category:1974 songs]]\n[[Category:Pope John Paul II]]\n[[Category:Internet memes]]\n\n\n{{1970s-song-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Orphan|date=July 2016}}\n\n'''Lord, You Have Come to the Lakeshore''', in some versions '''You Have Come to the Seashore''' (Spanish: ''Pescador de hombres'', \"Fisher of Men\") is a 1974 [[Spain|Spanish]] religious song by Ces\u00e1reo Gabar\u00e1in. It was translated into English by Gertrude C. Suppe, George Lockwood and Raquel Guti\u00e9rrez-Achon.<ref name=\"Hymn\">Hymn Society of America, ed. (1995). ''[https://books.google.com.ar/books?id=K28JAQAAMAAJ&q=%22Pescador+de+hombres%22+%22Ces%C3%A1reo+Gabar%C3%A1in%22&dq=%22Pescador+de+hombres%22+%22Ces%C3%A1reo+Gabar%C3%A1in%22&hl=es&sa=X&ei=gDz3U6vZOoq6ogS8ioKoDA&ved=0CGAQ6AEwCQ The Hymn. Volume 46]</ref>\n\nIt was [[Pope John Paul II]]'s favourite song.<ref name=\"Pijarzy\"/>, and the Polish lyrics (titled ''Barka'', \"The Barge\") were written by a [[Salesians of Don Bosco|Salesian of Don Bosco]] Stanis\u0142aw Szmidt also in 1974<ref name=\"Pijarzy\">{{cite web|url=http://www.pijarzy.pl/polecamy/w_wolnym_czasie/czy_wiesz_ze.../%22barka%22_-_ulubiona_piesn_jana_pawla_ii,_historia_piesni_d7353_pol.html|title=\"Barka\" - ulubiona pie\u015b\u0144 Jana Paw\u0142a II, historia pie\u015bni|first=|last=netsoftware.pl|publisher=}}</ref>. ''Barka'' was [[cover version|covered]] by [[catholic]] [[hardbass]] group ''XD Project''.<ref>[https://wykoprecords.bandcamp.com/track/barka-2 Hardbass Wadowice - Barka]</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Spanish songs]]\n[[Category:Christian songs]]\n[[Category:1974 songs]]\n[[Category:Pope John Paul II]]\n[[Category:Internet memes]]\n\n\n{{1970s-song-stub}}\n", "name_user": "89.228.84.38", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lord,_You_Have_Come_to_the_Lakeshore"}
{"title_page": "Shachokol", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2018}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                    = Shachokol\n| native_name             =\n| native_name_lang        =\n| settlement_type         = Village\n| image_skyline           =\n| image_alt               =\n| image_caption           =\n| etymology               =\n| pushpin_map             = India Ladakh#India\n| pushpin_map_caption     = Location in Ladakh, India\n| pushpin_map1            = India\n| pushpin_map_caption1    = Location in India\n| coordinates             = {{coord|33.9183387|N|78.3605653|E|display=inline,title}}\n| coordinates_footnotes   =\n| subdivision_type        = Country\n| subdivision_name        = [[India]]\n| subdivision_type1       = [[States and union territories of India|Union Territory]]\n| subdivision_name1       = [[Ladakh]]\n| subdivision_type2       = [[List of districts of India|District]]\n| subdivision_name2       = [[Leh district|Leh]]\n| subdivision_type3       = [[Tehsil]]\n| subdivision_name3       = [[Durbok|Durbuk]]\n| established_title       =\n| established_date        =\n| founder                 =\n| seat_type               = [[Panchayat]]\n| seat                    =\n| leader_party            =\n| leader_title            =\n| leader_name             =\n| unit_pref               = Metric\n| area_total_km2          =\n| elevation_m             = 5765\n| population_as_of        = 2011\n| population_total        = 888\n| population_density_km2  = auto\n| population_demonym      =\n| timezone1               = [[Indian Standard Time|IST]]\n| utc_offset1             = +5:30\n| postal_code_type        = <!-- [[Postal Index Number|PIN]] -->\n| postal_code             =\n| area_code_type          = <!-- [[Telephone numbers in India|STD Code]] -->\n| area_code               =\n| blank_name_sec1         = [[2011 Census of India|2011 census]] code\n| blank_info_sec1         = 875\n| footnotes               =\n}}\n\n'''Shachokol''' is a village in [[Leh district]] of the [[India]]n union territory of [[Ladakh]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://leh.nic.in/depts/villageamenitydirectory.pdf |title=Blockwise Village Amenity Directory |publisher=Ladakh Autonomous Hill Development Council |accessdate=2015-07-23 }}</ref> It is located in the [[Durbok|Durbuk]] [[tehsil]].\n\n==Demographics==\nAccording to the [[2011 census of India]], Shachokol has 147 households. The effective literacy rate (i.e. the literacy rate of population excluding children aged 6 and below) is 68.48%.<ref name=\"census_2011\"/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ Demographics (2011 Census)<ref name=\"census_2011\">{{cite news |url=http://www.censusindia.gov.in/datagov/CDB_PCA_Census/PCA_CDB_0103_F_Census.xls |title=Leh district census |work=[[2011 Census of India]] |publisher=Directorate of Census Operations |accessdate=2015-07-23 }}</ref>\n! !! Total !! Male !! Female\n|-\n| Population || 888 || 451 || 437\n|-\n| Children aged below 6 years || 98 || 47 || 51\n|-\n| [[Scheduled caste]] || 0 || 0 || 0\n|-\n| [[Scheduled tribe]] || 887 || 451 || 436\n|-\n| Literates || 541 || 320 || 221\n|-\n| Workers (all) || 489 || 267 || 222\n|-\n| Main workers (total) || 277 || 197 || 80\n|-\n| Main workers: Cultivators || 139 || 101 || 38\n|-\n| Main workers: Agricultural labourers || 4 || 3 || 1\n|-\n| Main workers: Household industry workers || 0 || 0 || 0\n|-\n| Main workers: Other || 134 || 93 || 41\n|-\n| Marginal workers (total) || 212 || 70 || 142\n|-\n| Marginal workers: Cultivators || 171 || 61 || 110\n|-\n| Marginal workers: Agricultural labourers || 8 || 0 || 8\n|-\n| Marginal workers: Household industry workers || 17 || 1 || 16\n|-\n| Marginal workers: Others || 16 || 8 || 8\n|-\n| Non-workers || 399 || 184 || 215\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Ladakh}}\n{{Leh district}}\n\n[[Category:Villages in Durbuk tehsil]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2018}}\n{{Inf