vens season|BAL]] \n| '''1''' || '''1''' || '''31''' || '''59''' || '''52.5''' || '''365''' || 6.2 || 1 || '''2''' || 63.2 || '''20''' || '''143''' || '''7.2''' || 0\n|-\n! colspan=2|Career !! 2 || 2 || 45 || 88 || 51.1 || 559 || 6.3 || 3 || 3 || 68.3 || 29 || 197 || 6.8 || 0\n|}\n\n== Awards and highlights==\n===College===\n====NCAA Football====\n* [[Heisman Trophy]] (2016)\n* [[Maxwell Award]] (2016)\n* [[Walter Camp Award]] (2016)\n* [[Associated Press College Football Player of the Year|Associated Press Player of the Year]] (2016)\n* [[Sporting News College Football Player of the Year|''Sporting News'' Player of the Year]] (2016)\n* Unanimous [[College Football All-America Team|All-American]] ([[2016 College Football All-America Team|2016]])\n* 2\u00d7 [[Atlantic Coast Conference football individual awards#Player of the Year|ACC Player of the Year]] (2016, 2017)\n* 2\u00d7 [[Atlantic Coast Conference football individual awards#Offensive Player of the Year|ACC Offensive Player of the Year]] (2016, 2017)\n* [[ACC Athlete of the Year]] (2018)\n* Total yards: 5261 (2017)<ref>{{cite web |title=2017 College Football Leaders |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/cfb/years/2017-leaders.html |website=sports-reference.com |publisher=Sports Reference College Football |accessdate=27 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n====[[Louisville Cardinals football]]====\n* Unanimous selection to [[Louisville Cardinals football|Louisville Cardinals]] Team of the Decade (2010-2019)<ref>{{cite web |last1=Rutherford |first1=Mike |title=Louisville Football team of the decade headlined by Lamar Jackson |url=https://www.cardchronicle.com/2019/12/23/21034743/louisville-football-team-of-the-decade-headlined-by-lamar-jackson |website=cardchronicle.com |publisher=CardChronicle SB Nation |accessdate=December 26, 2019}}</ref>\n* First [[Louisville Cardinals football|Louisville Cardinals]] quarterback named to [[College Football All-America Team|All-American]] team: ([[2016 College Football All-America Team|2016]])<ref>{{cite web |title=Louisville Cardinals All-America Selections |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/cfb/schools/louisville/all-america.html |website=sports-reference.com/ |publisher=Sports Reference |accessdate=27 January 2020}}</ref>\n* Most career rushing attempts by a quarterback: 655 (2015-2017)<ref name=\"qbrush\">{{cite web |title=Louisville Cardinals Passing |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/cfb/schools/louisville/passing.html |website=sports-reference.com |publisher=Sports Reference |accessdate=27 January 2020}}</ref>\n* Most career rushing yards: 4132 (2015-2017)<ref name=qbrush/><ref name=\"cardinalsrushing\">{{cite web |title=Louisville Cardinals Rushing |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/cfb/schools/louisville/rushing.html |website=sports-reference.com |publisher=Sports Reference |accessdate=27 January 2020}}</ref>\n* Most career rushing touchdowns: 50 (2015-2017)<ref name=qbrush/><ref name=cardinalsrushing/>\n* Most passing touchdowns in a game: 6 (tied with [[Chris Redman]]) (2016)<ref name=\"16CHAR\">{{Cite web|url = http://www.espn.com/ncf/recap/_/id/400869341|title = Lamar Jackson accounts for 8 TDs as Louisville routs Charlotte|date = 2016-09-01 |accessdate = |website = ESPN.com |publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref>\n\n===NFL===\n* [[National Football League Most Valuable Player Award|NFL Most Valuable Player]] ([[2019 NFL season|2019]])<ref name=\"2019nflmvp\">{{cite web|title=Lamar Jackson Unanimously Wins 2019 NFL MVP over Russell Wilson, Patrick Mahomes |url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2871478-lamar-jackson-unanimously-wins-2019-nfl-mvp-over-russell-wilson-patrick-mahomes |website=bleacherreport.com |accessdate= 1 February 2020}}</ref>\n* 5\u00d7 AFC Offensive Player of the Week (2019: Week 1, Week 9, Week 10, Week 12, Week 15)<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.baltimoreravens.com/news/lamar-jackson-wins-back-to-back-afc-offensive-player-of-the-week |title= Lamar Jackson Wins Back-to-Back AFC Offensive Player of the Week