jackson |website=cardchronicle.com |publisher=CardChronicle SB Nation |accessdate=December 26, 2019}}</ref>\n* First [[Louisville Cardinals football|Louisville Cardinals]] quarterback named to [[College Football All-America Team|All-American]] team: ([[2016 College Football All-America Team|2016]])<ref>{{cite web |title=Louisville Cardinals All-America Selections |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/cfb/schools/louisville/all-america.html |website=sports-reference.com/ |publisher=Sports Reference |accessdate=27 January 2020}}</ref>\n* Most career rushing attempts by a quarterback: 655 (2015-2017)<ref name=\"qbrush\">{{cite web |title=Louisville Cardinals Passing |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/cfb/schools/louisville/passing.html |website=sports-reference.com |publisher=Sports Reference |accessdate=27 January 2020}}</ref>\n* Most career rushing yards: 4132 (2015-2017)<ref name=qbrush/><ref name=\"cardinalsrushing\">{{cite web |title=Louisville Cardinals Rushing |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/cfb/schools/louisville/rushing.html |website=sports-reference.com |publisher=Sports Reference |accessdate=27 January 2020}}</ref>\n* Most career rushing touchdowns: 50 (2015-2017)<ref name=qbrush/><ref name=cardinalsrushing/>\n* Most passing touchdowns in a game: 6 (tied with [[Chris Redman]]) (2016)<ref name=\"16CHAR\">{{Cite web|url = http://www.espn.com/ncf/recap/_/id/400869341|title = Lamar Jackson accounts for 8 TDs as Louisville routs Charlotte|date = 2016-09-01 |accessdate = |website = ESPN.com |publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref>\n\n===NFL===\n* [[National Football League Most Valuable Player Award|NFL Most Valuable Player]] ([[2019 NFL season|2019]])<ref name=\"2019nflmvp\">{{cite web|title=Lamar Jackson Unanimously Wins 2019 NFL MVP over Russell Wilson, Patrick Mahomes |url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2871478-lamar-jackson-unanimously-wins-2019-nfl-mvp-over-russell-wilson-patrick-mahomes |website=bleacherreport.com |accessdate= 1 February 2020}}</ref>\n* 5\u00d7 AFC Offensive Player of the Week (2019: Week 1, Week 9, Week 10, Week 12, Week 15)<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.baltimoreravens.com/news/lamar-jackson-wins-back-to-back-afc-offensive-player-of-the-week |title= Lamar Jackson Wins Back-to-Back AFC Offensive Player of the Week | last=Brwon | first=Clifton |date=November 13, 2019 |website=Baltimore Ravens |language=en |access-date=November 13, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"week15\">{{cite web |last1=Bergman |first1=Jeremy |title=Lamar Jackson, Drew Brees among Players of the Week |url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000001089370/article/lamar-jackson-drew-brees-among-players-of-the-week |website=nfl.com |publisher=National Football League |accessdate=December 18, 2019}}</ref>\n* NFL Offensive Rookie of the Month (December 2018)<ref name=8Lamar/>\n* 2x AFC Offensive Player of the Month (December 2018)<ref>{{cite web |title=ALL-TIME AP HONORS |url=https://static.clubs.nfl.com/image/upload/v1579106497/ravens/x3fjvmsx34pdt26r821h.pdf |website=baltimoreravens.com |publisher=Baltimore Ravens |accessdate=3 February 2020}}</ref> (November 2019)<ref>{{cite web |last1=Gordon |first1=Grant |title=Lamar Jackson among Players of the Month for Nov. |url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000001084114/article/lamar-jackson-among-players-of-the-month-for-nov |website=nfl.com |publisher=The National Football League |accessdate=December 5, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[FedEx Air & Ground NFL Players of the Week|FedEx Air Player of the Year]] (2019)<ref>{{cite web |title=WINNERS: JACKSON & HENRY |url=http://www.nfl.com/voting/players-air-and-ground/2019/YEAR/0 |website=nfl.com |publisher=The National Football League |accessdate=2 February 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Pro Bowl]] ([[2020 Pro Bowl|2019]])<ref>{{cite web |title=NFL reveals rosters for 2020 Pro Bowl in Orlando |url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000001089218/article/nfl-reveals-rosters-for-2020-pro-bowl-in-orlando |website=nfl.com |publisher=National Football League |accessdate=Dec